File: Eskom is urging customers to use electricity sparingly. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will implement Stage 2 load-shedding between 8am and 10pm on Saturday. The power utility says this is so it can refill its emergency generation reserves to prepare for next week. READ: LOAD-SHEDDING: Schedules, info, and how it affects you South Africans began the month with Stage 2 load-shedding which escalated to Stage 4 as the power utility's system remained unreliable. Eskom is urging South Africans to use electricity sparingly.